al Whyte\r\nPaul Tucker\r\nStephen Austin\r\nJohn Burns\r\nWayne Byrne\r\nPaul Casson-Yardley\r\nJon Church-Fraser\r\nTrevor Fehin\r\nGraeme Ford\r\nJohn Micheal Foulger\r\nDeclan Geraghty\r\nGreg Jeloudov\r\nJimmy Keegan\r\nAndrew Kybett\r\nArnold Montey\r\nRana Morrison\r\nJer O\'Leary\r\nDerek Pykett', 'The story of a man with a free soul...and with the courage to follow it.\r\n\r\nWhat would drive a man to revolt against a king...and a country to fight at the side of such a man?\r\n\r\nWho does history remember? Those who beg for mercy? Or those who bleed for freedom?\r\n\r\nA man who gave his country the passion to fight hard...the will to bleed long...and the strength to die well.\r\n\r\nEvery man\'s spirit is free. Not every man has the courage to follow it.\r\n\r\nWhat gives men the will to fight hard...the strength to bleed long...the courage to die well?\r\n\r\nWhat sort of man would lead a revolt against a king...and what sort of country would fight beside such a man?\r\n\r\nNo Man Should Live In The Shadow Of The Crown\r\n\r\nWhat kind of man would defy a king?\r\n\r\nEvery man dies, not every man really lives.\r\n\r\nHis passion captivated a queen. His courage inspired a nation. His heart defied an empire.\r\n\r\nHe who fought, fought for freedom.', 'When his secret bride is executed for assaulting an English soldier who tried to rape her, William Wallace begins a revolt against King Edward I of England.', 'When his secret bride is executed for assaulting an English soldier who tried to rape her, William Wallace begins a revolt against King Edward I of England.\r\n-\r\nDaniel Williamson\r\n\r\nWilliam Wallace is a Scottish rebel who leads an uprising against the cruel English ruler Edward the Longshanks, who wishes to inherit the crown of Scotland for himself. When he was a young boy, William Wallace\'s father and brother, along with many others, lost their lives trying to free Scotland. Once he loses another of his loved ones, William Wallace begins his long quest to make Scotland free once and for all, along with the assistance of Robert the Bruce.\r\n-\r\nAnonymous\r\n\r\nTells the story of the legendary thirteenth century Scottish hero named William Wallace. Wallace rallies the Scottish against the English monarch and Edward I after he suffers a personal tragedy by English soldiers. Wallace gathers a group of amateur warriors that is stronger than any English army.\r\n-\r\nJwelch5742\r\n\r\nAround the end of the 1200s, oppressed by King Edward \"Longshanks\" who rules England with an iron fist, the noble and charismatic Scot of humble descent, William Wallace, leads a righteous campaign to end tyranny. In this gallant quest for freedom, the gifted strategist and mighty warrior will amass the hordes of the oppressed Scotsmen who thirst to reclaim their independence, however, the road to liberty is always drenched in blood.\r\n-\r\nNick Riganas\r\n\r\nIn 14th Century Scotland, William Wallace leads his people in a rebellion against the tyranny of the English King, who has given English nobility the \'Prima Nocta\' - a right to take all new brides for the first night. The Scots are none too pleased with the brutal English invaders, but they lack leadership to fight back. Wallace creates a legend of himself, with his courageous defense of his people and attacks on the English.\r\n-\r\nRob Hartill', 'Blu-ray', 1, 1, '', 0, '2020-05-01', '', '2020-04-14 10:35:05', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'Argentina::16\r\nAustralia::MA\r\nBelgium::KT/EA\r\nBrazil::16\r\nCanada::13+\r\nChile::14\r\nCzech Republic::15\r\nDenmark::15\r\nFinland::K-15/13\r\nFrance::Tous publics\r\nGermany::16\r\nGreece::K-15\r\nHong Kong::IIB\r\nHungary::16\r\nIceland::16\r\nIndia::A\r\nIreland::15\r\nItaly::T\r\nMalaysia::18SG\r\nMexico::C\r\nNetherlands::16\r\nNew Zealand::R16\r\nNigeria::18\r\nNorway::18\r\nPeru::14\r\nPhilippines::R-18\r\nPortugal::M/12\r\nRussia::16+\r\nSingapore::M18\r\nSouth Korea::15\r\nSpain::18\r\nSweden::15\r\nUnited Kin