 (Dutch Translation)\r\n\r\nWho\'s afraid of the Big Bad Gru? (French Translation)\r\n\r\nIn eye-popping Real 3D.\r\n\r\nIn eye-popping 3D. (UK release poster)\r\n\r\nBeing good is SO overrated. (UK release poster)', 'When a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme, he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.', 'When a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme, he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.\r\n-\r\nKenneth Chisholm\r\n\r\nIn a happy suburban neighborhood surrounded by white picket fences with flowering rose bushes, sits a black house with a dead lawn. Unbeknownst to the neighbors, hidden beneath this house is a vast secret hideout. Surrounded by a small army of minions, we discover Gru (Steve Carell), planning the biggest heist in the history of the world. He is going to steal the moon. Gru delights in all things wicked. Armed with his arsenal of shrink rays, freeze rays, and battle-ready vehicles for land and air, he vanquishes all who stand in his way. Until the day he encounters the immense will of three little orphaned girls who look at him and see something that no one else has ever seen: a potential Dad. The world\'s greatest villain has just met his greatest challenge: three little girls named Margo (Miranda Cosgrove), Edith (Dana Gaier), and Agnes (Elsie Fisher).\r\n-\r\nUniversal Pictures\r\n\r\nThis follows the story of Gru (Steve Carell), a supervillain who adopts three girls from an orphanage; and Vector (Jason Segel), a rival of Gru who steals the Great Pyramid of Giza. When Gru learns of Vector\'s heist, he plans an even greater heist: to shrink and steal the Earth\'s moon.\r\n-\r\nDok Calculus\r\n\r\nWith a flair for high-profile crime and devising all sorts of nefarious schemes, mankind\'s undisputed public enemy number one, and history\'s most despicable supervillain, Gru (Steve Carell), finds himself in a real predicament when Vector (Jason Segel), his cunning archrival manages to outshine him. Now, only an outrageously ambitious plan involving the snatching of the moon, three adorable cookie-selling orphaned sisters - and most importantly - the devastating shrink-ray gun can help Gru earn a place in the pantheon of mega-criminals. But is this going to be a walk in the park for the sweet scoundrel with the heart of gold?\r\n-\r\nNick Riganas\r\n\r\nSupervillain Gru (Steve Carell) is determined to pull off the crime of the century after being humiliated by his rival Vector (Jason Segel) after he stole the Pyramid of Giza. Gru hatches a plan that involves taking advantage of three orphan girls (Miranda Cosgrove, Dana Gaier, Elsie Fisher) and their cookie selling business. However, he soon finds that these girls see him more as a potential father, and soon finds that he is in over his head.', 'Blu-ray', 1, 1, '', 0, '2020-05-01', '', '2020-04-14 10:42:33', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 'Argentina::Atp\r\nAustralia::PG\r\nBrazil::Livre\r\nCanada::PG\r\nFinland::K-7\r\nFrance::Tous publics\r\nGermany::0\r\nGreece::K-10\r\nIndonesia::SU\r\nIreland::G\r\nJapan::G\r\nLithuania::V\r\nMalaysia::U\r\nMexico::AA\r\nNetherlands::6\r\nNew Zealand::PG\r\nNorway::A\r\nPeru::Apt\r\nPhilippines::G\r\nPortugal::M/6\r\nRussia::0+\r\nSingapore::PG\r\nSouth Africa::PG\r\nSouth Korea::All\r\nSpain::A/i\r\nSweden::7\r\nSwitzerland::0\r\nTaiwan::GP\r\nUnited Kingdom::PG\r\nUnited States::TV-G', 0),
