. With the help of Griffin (Michael Stuhlbarg), a being who can see all timelines, they track Boris down. J also learns a secret, something old Agent K (Tommy Lee Jones) had never told him.\r\n-\r\ngarykmcd\r\n\r\nWhen Boris the Animal (Jemaine Clement), an alien who is the last of his race, is confined to LunarMax, a penal colony on the moon, he escapes and goes to Earth to get the man who placed him there, M.I.B. Agent K (Tommy Lee Jones). He confronts K, K and J (Will Smith) corner him, but he disappears. J asks K who he is, but K doesn\'t want to say anything. J goes to M.I.B. Headquarters and learns who Boris is, but before he could learn more, the Agent in charge, O (Dame Emma Thompson), stops him. The next day, J goes to pick up K, but finds someone else living at his apartment. When he goes to M.I.B., he looks for K, but everyone there tells him, K died in 1969 after tackling with Boris. But J says K captured him. That\'s when alien vessels which are from Boris\' planet show up, and they\'re about to devour the Earth. But J says that K placed a barrier that keeps them from entering Earth in 1969, which would lead to their extinction. It\'s obvious that Boris went back in time and killed K before he could deploy the barrier. So J goes to see an alien on Earth whose father was also at the penal colony, who J assumes told Boris that he worked on time travel and his son has the device. J goes to see him and tells him about the invasion. So he sends J back just before K\'s death. J arrives in 1969 and fails to stop Boris and is captured by the younger K (Josh Brolin) who asks him who he is, and what is he doing here. J was told not to tell him anything. But with time running out J tells him, but K doesn\'t believe him at first, so they go out to stop Boris. Only problem, J doesn\'t exactly know what happened, so he\'s not sure where they should go.\r\n-\r\nrcs0411@yahoo.com\r\n\r\nCriminal Boris the Animal (Jemaine Clement) escapes from LunarMax, a moon-based maximum security prison. He comes to Earth seeking revenge on Agent K (Tommy Lee Jones), who shot off his arm and arrested him forty years ago, and protected Earth from a Boglodyte invasion. Boris is defeated again, and he travels back in time to 1969 to kill Agent K (Josh Brolin). When Agent J notes that the timeline has changed in the present day and Agent O (Dame Emma Thompson) tells him that K died in 1969, he decides to travel to July 15, 1969 to save K the following day. Agent J has difficulties to convince the Young Agent K with lies, but when he decides to tell the truth, K believes in his words and they seek out Boris together. They are helped by the amicable alien Griiffin (Jemaine Clement), who has precognitive powers and gives the ArcNet to K to protect Earth from the Boglodyte invasion. Furthermore, J learns a secret about K and himself.\r\n-\r\nClaudio Carvalho, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil\r\n\r\nAgents J (Will Smith) and K (Tommy Lee Jones) have seen some inexplicable things in Agent J\'s fourteen years with the Men In Black intelligence agency. When an alien assassin by the name of Boris the Animal (Jemaine Clement) escapes from the LunarMax prison, all bets are off. Time travel has been discovered and Boris tracks down the people who are responsible for creating it. Boris travels back in time to 1969 - the year that Agent K had shot off his arm and deployed a shield that led to Boris\' race\'s extinction. As Agent J delves deep into the case, he soon finds himself travelling back to 1969. There, he meets the young Agent K (Josh Brolin) - who is every bit as awkward and demeaning as the elder Agent K is. J and K have their differences, but soon discovers that Boris has a much more sinister motive than originally thought. With the help of an alien super being named Griffin who can see into alternate realities, J and K begin a pursuit of Boris The Animal that takes them to Cape Canaveral, Florida just in time for the Apollo 11 launch. There, secrets that could change time and space forever are revealed.\r\n-\r\nhalo1k\r\n\r\nAfter nearly four decades of imprisonment, the hideous extraterrestrial and Agent K\'s arch-nemesis, Boris the Animal, manages to escape the lunar maximum-security prison, Lunar Max, bent on revenge. With this in mind, the powerful alien travels back in time to 1969, where a fresh and inexperienced version of a young Agent K exists; however, Agent J, too, takes a step back in history, teaming up with his old/new taciturn companion, to thwart the interplanetary visitor\'s evil schemes. Nevertheless, can this brand-new team of reluctant partners re-establish order and peace in the universe?\r\n-\r\nNick Riganas', 'Blu-ray', 1, 1, '', 0, '0000-00-00', '', '2020-08-26 14:32:44', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 'Argentina::13\r\nAustralia::M\r\nBrazil::10\r\nCanada::PG\r\nFinland::K-12\r\nFrance::Tous publics\r\nGermany::12\r\nHong Kong::IIA\r\nIndia::UA\r\nIreland::PG\r\nItaly::T\r\nJapan::G\r\nMalaysia::P13\r\nMexico::A\r\nMongolia::PG\r\nNetherlands::9\r\nNew Zealand::M\r\nNorway::11\r\nPeru::14\r\nPhilippines::PG-13\r\nPoland::12\r\nPortugal::M/12\r\nRussia::12+\r\nSingapore::PG\r\nSouth Africa::13\r\nSouth Korea::12\r\nSpain::7\r\nSweden::11\r\nSwitzerland::12\r\nUnited Kingdom::PG\r\nUnited States::PG-13\r\nVietnam::P', 12),
